FBIS4-43757 "drweu119_q_94009" FBIS-WEU-94-119 Daily Report 18 Jun 1994 TURKEY Bomb Explosions, Casualties Reported Bomb Explosions, Casualties Reported Bomb Explodes at Travel Agency TA1806151794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1200 GMT 18 Jun 94 TA1806151794 Ankara TRT Television Network Turkish BFN [Announcer-read report over video] [Text] A bomb exploded in the cargo department of a travel agency in Kadikoy, Istanbul, causing material damage. No one was killed or injured in the incident. An explosion occurred around 0945 this morning in the cargo department of a travel agency on Kadikoy's Rihtim Street. The explosion shattered the glass and triggered a fire. Firefighters extinguished the fire before it spread any further. Officials reported that a bus left for Harem shortly before the explosion and a bag believed to have been forgotten by the passengers was taken to the cargo department. Officials noted that a bomb which was inside the bag exploded and that a 27-28-year-old- woman, who is believed to have left the bag, is being sought.
